                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7701: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-02T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1926—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 2—9:46 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>447. My 438, September 29, 3 p.m. Following from American consul general at
                    Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 1, 1 p.m. In accordance with your telegram of September 21, 5
                            p.m., I filed protest with Eugene Chen on September 25th, to which he
                            has now replied. The substance has been telegraphed to Commander in
                            Chief Chiang Chung-cheng for his information and action.</p>
                        <p>Chen declines to admit the regulations restricting navigation on the
                            Yangtze are in violation of the treaties. He declares that as war is now
                            raging in the Wuhan area foreign men-of-war should withdraw as
                            requested, stating he also expresses the hope that American men-of-war
                            will comply with the regulations to proceed to certain designated
                            places, anchor and notify the military authorities of their nationality
                            in order that appropriate action may be taken. Despatch will be
                            forwarded with copies of correspondence”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
